result.execSummary:
The defendant Jasmine C Williams was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia [Modifiers: Repeater], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jasmine C Williams in court with attorney Brian F. Bennett.  Jill Laufenberg appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 16CF59 and 15CF204 @ 9:31 a.m. Agreement stated - Def will waive prelim hrgs on both, informations filed. Def will plead to 16CF59 cts 1 & 3, cts 2 & 4 dismiss and read in, 15CF204 ct 2, ct 1 dismiss and read in. 16CF59 2 yrs probation on each, AODA and follow through, court costs, 5 days jail on each, consecutive. 15CF204 -  withheld sentence, 2 yrs probation, court costs. Bonds in both to be applied to costs. Atty Bennett agrees. If revoked, 6 days credit on 16CF59 and 1 day credit on 15CF204. Discussion regarding need for prelim waivers and amendment of Ct 3 of 16CF59. Court reviews preliminary hearing rights with Defendant, finds waivers knowing and voluntary. Court reviews plea quest. 15CF204 ct 2 - no contest plea. 16CF59 ct 1 - no contest plea, ct 3 as amended in information - no contest plea. 15CF204 ct 1 - dismissed and read in. 16CF59 cts 2 & 4 dismissed and read in. Constitutional rights, elements (Def admits prior convictions), possible penalties reviewed. Atty Bennett satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds guilty of 15CF204 ct 2 and 16CF59 ct 1 and ct 3. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. Nothing by Defendant. Court questions Defendant. Sentencing remarks by the Court, will follow agreement. 15CF204 ct 2 - withheld sentence, 2 yrs probation, AODA and follow through, court costs, credit for 1 day if revoked. DNA sample and surcharge. Bond will be applied to costs. 16CF59 ct 1 - withheld sentence, 2 yrs probation, AODA and follow through, any counseling as required, 5 days jail, report no later than 7 p.m. on 9/1/16. May serve in another county. Huber. Credit for 6 days served if revoked. Court costs, DNA sample and surcharge. Apply bond. Ct 3 - same sentence as ct 1, withheld, 2 yrs probation, 5 days jail, consecutive to ct 1, huber, may serve in another county. No electronic monitoring. Court costs, DNA surcharge. Credit for 6 days if revoked. Discussion regarding cell phone. State does not object to return.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. State has complied with victim's rights. Postconviction rights.
Plea/sentencing hearing on July 20, 2016 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Jasmine C Williams in court with attorney Brian F. Bennett.  Jill Laufenberg appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Cases called 15CF204 and 16CF59.  15CF204 Bond forfeiture hearing.  Statement by Atty Laufenberg.  State request this matter be adjourned until later.  Response by Atty Bennett.  Court reserve ruling on bond forfeiture.  Both cases set for status conf.  Status conference scheduled for June 6, 2016 at 03:30 pm.
